2/27/01
  Study of forced switch using NCube server:
    Noted that the last splice always has forced switch.
    Figured out that the forced switch is due to tsDelay exceeding the
      MAX_TS_DELAY.  The last ad actually has an overlap with the
      previous ad of 160 ms.  When the previous ad's tsDelay is accounted for,
      the overall tsDelay for the last ad exceeds MAX_TS_DELAY of 250 ms.
      As a result, there are drop ad frames, which results in forced switch
      at the end.
    Since the final API will use time-based anyway, instead of fixing this
    problem, I would simply add an NCUBE flag to consider EOS in the
    exitCandidate condition in picture-based mode.

  Emma's test:
    There is one DPI reset in 0227-61-4.log.  Seems like there is a timebase
    jump in the foreground channel causing it to become ready.  However, in
    procEntryPoint(), a huge gap of more than 4 sec is detected.  This cause
    the routine to continuously insert glue pictures, using up all the
    PidBufs!  This fianlly cause a Bad PidBuf pointer problem and trap.

    - Should we fix this problem by checking potential gap problem before
      entering into procEntryPoint()??


