Support of component splice mode:
  For bypass component, we don't need to do any switch, but we need to
  retag the elementary stream to a different channel.  The idea is:

     Elementary stream should not point to its corresponding chan.
     Instead, direction should always be from chan to pidChan.
     All elementary stream level process should not based on Chan.
     This way the channel retagging should be simple.

  This is the way it is done currently.  Need to check with new audio code.


Support of splicing when primary has no valid input:
  Need a way to tell whether a channel has valid input or not.
  Invalid condition:
    - scrambled video
    - lost video signal

  (May be in output task, use lastPicStat==pPicStat to determine whether the
   last picture has been sent.)
  For time based, only BG ready is needed.
  For pic based, ?
  For EOS based, ?


